    "description": "Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Asia Pacific Associates has an exciting opening for a Radiologist at our Visakhapatnam office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Asia Pacific Associates:\nGlenmark Pharmaceuticals Asia Pacific Associates is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Glenmark Pharmaceuticals Asia Pacific Associates!",
